channel.title: Hamachi Servers?
channel.description: I have a hamachi server, but it wont run the customs i made, there just nulls. It's a 317 server. All my customs are nulls, how do i make the customs work? Thanks!

item.title: Hamachi Servers?
item.dc:creator: @Xillion Xillion
item.description:
@Xillion wrote:

[quote=“Diablo Runes, post:3, topic:327374”][quote author=Xillion link=topic=423762.msg3112600#msg3112600 date=1264657528]
You need to add the models into your client
[/quote]
not just that, you need to add the models into the clients folder, Models. Once you have put your models in that folder, you have to add the ints into Class8.java. Once you have done that go into your server and type add models (model number) or which ever your command is, exit the client, then compile. Start up your client again, do ::pickup (id) (ammount) then your item should be there![/quote]You forgot to mention that part how you need to put it in item.cfg and item.java…

item.title: Hamachi Servers?
item.dc:creator: @Diablo_Runes Diablo Runes
item.description:
@Diablo_Runes wrote:

Xillion:

You need to add the models into your client

not just that, you need to add the models into the clients folder, Models. Once you have put your models in that folder, you have to add the ints into Class8.java. Once you have done that go into your server and type add models (model number) or which ever your command is, exit the client, then compile. Start up your client again, do ::pickup (id) (ammount) then your item should be there!
